<h2>Canadian Influence</h2>

<p>
Concerns about American influence have risen sharply over recent decades, but Windsor's pizza has helped maintain an identity and even sprinkle Canadian influence into America. For example, an Armando's pizza recently opened in Clawson, Michigan. This location brings the signature Windsor-style pizza with shredded and canned mushrooms to America. Although it is in the Windsor style, it lacks the signature Galati Cheese due to border restrictions. The availability of Windsor pizza in Detroit signifies recognition of Windsor-style pizza, and more food lovers are eager to try it. Americans have increasingly wanted to try Windsor's pizza, and according to Joe, even come to Windsor for Pizza tours as part of various travel excursions. Although big chains do exist within Windsor, as Bob from Arcata identified, establishments like Domino's and Little Caesars are not their competition. Windsor Pizza has created its own collective identity based on family traditions, quality, and relationships.
</p>

</div>

